<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880210-0058 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Maxus Energy Corp. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> MXS </CO><TEXT>   Maxus Energy Corp., Dallas, said it plans to increase its exploration and development budget 13% to $241 million this year from $214 million in 1987.    The oil and gas exploration and production concern said the increase is attributable to a stepped-up exploration program in Indonesia.    Maxus also said it replaced 93% of its world-wide oil and gas production with new reserves in 1987. World-wide reserves at year end were 281.2 million oil-equivalent barrels, the company said. </TEXT></DOC>